@startuml use-case-diagram
' Figure 1 of 2. Figure 2: use-case-diagram-part2.puml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam titleFontSize 15
skinparam titleFontStyle bold
skinparam ArrowColor #2E5A88
skinparam usecaseBackgroundColor #E8F0FE
skinparam usecaseBorderColor #2E5A88
skinparam usecaseFontColor #102040
skinparam usecaseFontSize 11
skinparam actorFontSize 12
skinparam actorFontStyle bold
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9E3
skinparam noteBorderColor #C9A227
skinparam noteFontSize 10
skinparam nodesep 55
skinparam ranksep 50

title Stock Guard - Use case diagram 1 of 2\nAccess, inventory, usage, and risk
left to right direction

actor "Operational\nStaff" as OS
actor "System\nAdministrator" as ADM
actor "Strategic (Business\nOwner and Stock\nAnalyst)" as ST

package "Operations" {
  usecase "Authenticate" as p1A
  usecase "View dashboard" as p1B
  usecase "Manage inventory" as p1C
  usecase "Log inventory usage" as p1D
  usecase "View risk alerts" as p1E
}

OS  --> p1A
OS  --> p1B
OS  --> p1C
OS  --> p1D
OS  --> p1E

ADM --> p1A
ADM --> p1B
ADM --> p1C
ADM --> p1D
ADM --> p1E

ST  --> p1A
ST  --> p1B
ST  --> p1C
ST  --> p1E

note right of p1D
  TAC story 1. ``POST /api/inventory/usage`` -
  update **Inventory**, insert **UsageLog**
end note

note bottom of p1A
  **Strategic** roles: no *Log usage* in
  app. **Diagram 2 of 2:** use-case-diagram-part2 (PNG in same folder)
end note

@enduml